:","from <i>spina</i> ‘thorn, thorn bush’, used as a nickname in various senses, including ‘distress, sorrow’ (alluding to Christ's crown of thorns), and also as a personal name; or alternatively a habitational name from any of numerous places called with this word (in some instances with reference to the dedication of a shrine)."]}]},{"name":"Moroello","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Angelo, Antonio, Gaetano, Rocco, Carmela, Carmine, Cesare, Filippo, Luciano, Silvio, Aldo.","Italian (southern):","from a pet form or diminutive of   Moro  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Morella","meanings":["form of French <b>Mireille</b>."]},{"name":"Moro","meanings":["‘Peach’."]},{"name":"Morelli","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Antonio, Aldo, Luigi, Remo, Carmine, Rocco, Salvatore, Domenic, Gino, Dino, Domenico.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Morello  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Moroello Malaspina was born about 1140, in Italy, his father, Marchese Obizzo Malaspina, was 29 and his mother, Maria Bianco, was 26. He married Una Frangipane. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1197, in his hometown, at the age of 58."},"et":{"about 1140–1197":"umbes 1140–1197","1140–1193":"1140–1193","1140–1197":"1140–1197","1160–1210":"1160–1210","1145–1202":"1145–1202","1165–1206":"1165–1206","1171–1220":"1171–1220","1172–1193":"1172–1193","–1225":"–1225","1112–1185":"1112–1185","1115–1190":"1115–1190","1190":"1190","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1165":"1165","1220":"1220","1197":"1197","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1172":"1172","1193":"1193","1171":"1171","1160":"1160","ABT 1172":"umbes 1172","1206":"1206","1115":"1115","1225":"1225","1202":"1202","1112":"1112","1145":"1145","1210":"1210","after 1185":"pärast 1185","ABT 1171":"umbes 1171","Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italy":"Correggio, Ferrara, Ferra